article.headline: IPFW 79, Western Illinois 77
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. (AP) -- Jaraun Burrows scored 23 points and made the game-winning layup to lead IPFW to a 79-77 victory over Western Illinois on Tuesday. DeWitt Scott came off the bench to score 18 points on 7-of-13 shooting and Jakari Johnson added 11 points and seven assists for the Mastodons (6-11). Burrows blocked two shots in the final 49 seconds and broke a 77-77 tie with a basket with two seconds left. Western Illinois' David Jackson missed a potential game-winning 3-pointer at the buzzer. Jerryck Owens-Murrey led Western Illinois with a career-high 26 points on 9-of-10 shooting as the Leathernecks (4-12) finished 27-of-59 (46 percent) from the floor. Xavier Price added 14 points off the bench for Western Illinois.
